## TITLE RULES

Questions and bold statements. Stop the scroll.

**Good:**
- "Breaking Bad is the best Economics case study ever made — and it's not even close"
- "The scene in Oppenheimer that perfectly explains IB History's unit on the Cold War"
- "Parasite predicted everything your Economics teacher is trying to explain"

**Bad:**
- "Breaking Bad — Supply and Demand" ← sounds like a homework title
- "How Interstellar teaches us about physics" ← too bland

